Business Brief -- Alex. Brown Inc.:
   Concern's Earnings Increased
   In the 4th Period and Year
Alex. Brown said it was a top underwriter of initial
public offerings last year and also managed a significant
number of successful financings for existing public
companies.
   For the year, net rose to $52 million, or $3.36 a share,
from $7.8 million, or 50 cents a share. Revenue rose to
$410.6 million from $271.7 million.
   Investment banking revenue rose 66% to $152.9 million.
Transaction revenue, spurred by over-the-counter and
municipal trading, more than doubled to $83.5 million.
Commission revenue rose 38% to $94 million. Assets under
management increased 19% to $7.6 billion at Dec. 31.